NATS
National Airspace Trajectory-Prediction System
Ground Vehicle TRX File and Driving Plan

Format

The format of this TRX file is illustrated below. It has the following three rows:

  • TRACK_TIME
  • TRACK: This row has the initial state.
  • FP_ROUTE: This is the driving plan.

Let's use an example for more detail.

TRACK_TIME 1121238067
TRACK FIRE123 SWA1897 373716.896 1222324.18 20 13 28
FP_ROUTE KSFO.<{"id": "Gate_F_086"}, {"id": "Ramp_06_011"}, {"id": "Txy_A_B1"}, {"id": "Txy_A_016"}, {"id": "Txy_A_015"}, {"id": "Txy_A_012"}, {"id": "Txy_A_011"}, {"id": "Txy_A_D"}, {"id": "Txy_A_010"}, {"id": "Txy_A_E"}, {"id": "Txy_A_009"}, {"id": "Txy_A_F1"}, {"id": "Txy_A_008"}, {"id": "Txy_A_G"}, {"id": "Txy_A_007"}, {"id": "Txy_A_006"}, {"id": "Txy_A_005"}, {"id": "Txy_A_H"}, {"id": "Txy_A_004"}, {"id": "Txy_A_M"}, {"id": "Txy_A_003"}, {"id": "Txy_A_002"}, {"id": "Txy_A_A1"}, {"id": "Txy_A_001"}>

TRACK_TIME 1121238067
Departure time of the ground vehicle.

FIRE123
Ground Vehicle ID.

SWA1897
Aircraft being serviced by ground vehicle.

373716.896 1222324.18
atitude and longitude of the vehicle’s initial position(Degree Minute Second format).The latitude and longitude format is in degree-minute-second. For high accuracy, using decimal digit for second value is acceptable, like 373638.1234.

20 13 28
The vehicle’s initial speed, altitude (Airport Elevation), and heading.

KSFO
Airport where the ground vehicle is operating.
